tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control (prediabetes/early diabetes). Creatinine is slightly below normal, which is not clinically significant. Total CO₂ is mildly decreased, possibly suggesting mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and monitoring of glycemic status.
